The Department of Energy (DOE), by memo dated 05/13/2014, has granted Sandia permission to assert its copyright in 
software entitled "Nalu v 1.0".

In accordance with the DOE's permission:

All copies of "Nalu v 1.0" that are released under an Open Source Software (OSS) license should be marked:

Copyright (2014) Sandia Corporation. Under the terms of Contract DE-AC04-94AL85000 with Sandia Corporation, 
the U.S. Government retains certain rights in this software.

When the first code is committed to the repository, the full license language will be provided.
